The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 April is 272,903 (31,453.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 April, there were 2,018 new confirmed cases (232.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 April, there were 3,099 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 35% (1,081 fewer cases).
